'''薩羅納'''（{{lang-grc|Σάλωνα}}，{{lang-en|Salona}}）是位於[[克羅埃西亞|克羅埃西亞]]達爾馬提亞海岸的一個考古遺址<ref>{{Citation |publisher = J. Murray |publication-place = London |author = R. Lambert Playfair |url = http://openlibrary.org/books/OL16538259M/Handbook_to_the_Mediterranean |title = Handbook to the Mediterranean |edition = 3rd |publication-date = 1892 |chapterurl = https://archive.org/stream/handbooktomedit01firgoog#page/n41/mode/2up |chapter = Salona |accessdate = 2018-11-17 |archive-date = 2020-11-24 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201124024858/https://openlibrary.org/books/OL16538259M/Handbook_to_the_Mediterranean |dead-url = no }}</ref>。

薩羅納是古代[[伊利里亞人|伊利里亞人]]的都市<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://w3.mrki.info/split/solin.html |title=Solin early history |access-date=2015-10-05 |archive-date=2021-04-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210411215909/http://w3.mrki.info/split/solin.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。在[[羅馬人|羅馬人]]征服這裡之後，薩羅納成為[[達爾馬提亞_(羅馬行省)|達爾馬提亞]]的首府<ref>John Everett-Heath. "Dalmatia." ''Concise Dictionary of World Place-Names''. Oxford University Press. 2005. Encyclopedia.com</ref>。公元7世纪，萨罗纳在[[阿瓦尔人|阿瓦尔人]]和[[斯拉夫人|斯拉夫人]]的入侵中被摧毁。萨罗纳的难民逃往[[斯普利特|斯普利特]]的[[戴克里先宫|戴克里先宫]]避难，萨罗纳因而被废弃<ref>{{cite book |author1=Thomas of Split |title=History of the Bishops of Salona and Split |date=2006 |publisher=Central European University Press}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |editor=Charles George Herbermann |title=The Catholic Encyclopedia: An International Work of Reference |date=1913 |publisher=Universal Knowledge Foundation |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=WMyftgEACAAJ&hl=zh-CN&pg=PP1#v=onepage&q&f=false}}</ref>。

